# Snyk policy file for the cowork repository.
#
# This file lists explicit, justified suppressions for Snyk findings
# that we have reviewed and accepted as architecturally required. Every
# entry MUST include a `reason:` and an `expires:` date so the policy
# is re-reviewed periodically (default cadence: 12 months).
#
# Customer hand-off note: the cowork web Docker image (the artifact
# the customer actually pulls) does NOT contain the Electron sources
# in `src/main/`, so Electron-only Snyk Code findings against
# `oauth-service.ts`, `index.ts`, `index.html` etc. do not appear in
# the customer's Snyk Container scan. They are kept out of this file
# intentionally — there is nothing to suppress for the image-only
# threat model.
#
# Workstream A of the Snyk remediation pass closed every visible High
# in the Python server (server/main.py, server/routes/utilities.py,
# server/routes/artifacts.py, server/routes/attachments.py,
# server/routes/integrations.py) by hardening the existing guards
# rather than suppressing — so the `ignore:` map below is currently
# empty. Add entries here only when refactoring is impractical and
# the construct is genuinely required.

version: v1.25.0

# See `.trivyignore` (sibling file, repo root) for the equivalent
# Trivy/Aqua CVE allowlist — same rationale per CVE, same review cadence.
# When Snyk Container surfaces one of those CVEs under a Snyk-specific
# rule ID, mirror it here with the matching reason text.

ignore: {}

patch: {}
